name: kidney rhabdoid cancer
definition: A embryonal cancer that is located in the kidney. [url:http\://www.childrenshospital.org/az/Site1526/mainpageS1526P0.html]

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, a human malignant rhabdoid kidney tumor cell line was sensitive to UAB30 in both culture and in xenograft models, demonstrating cell-cycle arrest, decreased cell proliferation, apoptosis, and reduced tumor growth (PMID: 26873726).

references.title: Preclinical Evaluation of UAB30 in Pediatric Renal and Hepatic Malignancies.

clinicalTrials.title: A Phase 1 Study of the EZH2 Inhibitor Tazemetostat in Pediatric Subjects With Relapsed or Refractory INI1-Negative Tumors or Synovial Sarcoma
